question: What do you think is the biggest advantage of Variator compared to baseline models as shown in table 1 in the article 'Variator: Accelerating Pre-trained Models with Plug-and-Play Compression Modules'? Please briefly describe the working principle of LTP, which is one of the baseline models.
answer_format: Your answer should be a brief text.

eval_kwargs.reference_answer: The biggest advantage of Variator is its minimal additional parameters. LTP works by adaptively removing unimportant tokens based on attention scores, pruning tokens below a learned threshold for each layer.
